Content:
[telegram] <Regnar> Okay just relax a second man, you have your seed phrase correct? The 12 or 24 words that you were shown when you created your wallet. Those give you access no matter the wallet you use, desktop or mobile.
If you are on desktop, open "Lite" mode and use the restore wallet button, it will ask you for your seed, make sure you put it in perfectly. Itll then ask you to name the wallet and give it a password. 
Native mode doesn't use seeds, it downloads the whole blockchain which will take a long time.
Mobile will also ask you for your seed. I'm not up to date on the agama bugs right now, if there is a grey screen bug, but if you have your seed, you have your funds. (re @CRYPTOCHAOS: I enter my pass after the qr code and I dont think I named it and i cant get in can anyione help)
